<item>
            <title>[HBASE-46] Robust start and stop for cluster, regionserver</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-46</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a new region server is started, it should have a period during which it will retry to connect to the master, rather than just immediately shutting down when it can&apos;t contact the master.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, when HBase and HDFS are started at around the same time, HBase shouldn&apos;t immediately exit. Instead, wait a little while for everything to come online.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
